{% extends "demo.html.j2" %}

{% block head_extra %}
<link rel="stylesheet" href="{{ asset_base | default('') }}assets/pages/e3.css">
{% endblock %}

{% macro passage_list(title, rows, note='') %}
<section class="e3-retriever">
  <h3>{{ title }}</h3>
  {% if note %}<p class="e3-retriever__note">{{ note }}</p>{% endif %}
  <ol>
    {% for row in rows[:3] %}
    <li>
      <strong>{{ row.rank }}. {{ row.doc_id }}</strong>
      <p>{{ row.text }}</p>
      <span class="provenance-chip">{{ row.provenance.source_doc }} · {{ row.provenance.as_of }}</span>
      <span class="provenance-chip">{{ row.provenance.source_span }}</span>
    </li>
    {% endfor %}
  </ol>
</section>
{% endmacro %}

{% block demo_content %}
<section class="exhibit-intro" aria-label="What this exhibit shows">
  <h2 class="exhibit-intro__title">What this exhibit shows</h2>
  <div class="exhibit-intro__block">
    <h3 class="exhibit-intro__sub">What you are looking at</h3>
    <p>A sourced memory layer for {{ card_data.meta.manager_name }}. The active product is
      document-native preparation and deterministic hybrid search. The graph is shown only as
      a candidate evaluation because its formal gate has not cleared.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="exhibit-intro__block">
    <h3 class="exhibit-intro__sub">How to read it</h3>
    <ul class="exhibit-intro__list">
      <li>Click a typed node or edge to inspect the exact source sentence and date.</li>
      <li>Compare lexical, plain-hybrid, and graph-candidate top-three results as an
        <em>illustration</em>, then read the separate formal recall-at-ten refusal.</li>
      <li>The meeting brief names missing source panels rather than borrowing data from a
        different fictional manager.</li>
      <li>Read the full <a href="{{ asset_base | default('') }}specs/{{ card.id }}.html">method
        spec</a> for the schema, ranking math, and kill criterion.</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="e3-active" aria-labelledby="e3-active-title">
  <div>
    <p class="e3-kicker">Shipping fallback</p>
    <h2 id="e3-active-title">Active retrieval: hybrid search</h2>
    <p>Extraction tables and sourced hybrid search remain useful without production graph
      expansion. The graph result below is <strong>candidate — gate not cleared</strong>.</p>
  </div>
  <span class="verdict-chip" data-verdict="shrink">hybrid fallback active</span>
</section>

<section class="e3-panel" aria-labelledby="e3-graph-title">
  <header class="e3-panel__head">
    <div>
      <p class="e3-kicker">Candidate evaluation only</p>
      <h2 id="e3-graph-title">Typed manager-memory graph</h2>
    </div>
    <span class="verdict-chip" data-verdict="noise">candidate — gate not cleared</span>
  </header>
  <p>The manager record is <strong>Tier R</strong>, granted 2024-01. The
    <code>employed_by</code> edge from Elena Voss to Selby Point Advisors makes the
    person-across-firms path visible, but v1 never expands through a theme-based second hop.</p>
  <div class="e3-graph-grid">
    <div>
      <h3>Nodes</h3>
      <div class="e3-facts">
      {% for node in card_data.graph_candidate.nodes %}
        <button class="e3-fact" type="button" data-node-type="{{ node.node_type }}"
          data-source-doc="{{ node.provenance.source_doc }}"
          data-source-span="{{ node.provenance.source_span }}"
          data-as-of="{{ node.provenance.as_of }}">
          <span>{{ node.node_type }}</span><strong>{{ node.label }}</strong>
          {% if node.tier %}<small>Tier {{ node.tier }} · granted {{ node.tier_grant_date }}</small>{% endif %}
        </button>
      {% endfor %}
      </div>
    </div>
    <div>
      <h3>Edges</h3>
      <div class="e3-facts">
      {% for edge in card_data.graph_candidate.edges %}
        <button class="e3-fact" type="button" data-edge-type="{{ edge.edge_type }}"
          data-source-doc="{{ edge.provenance.source_doc }}"
          data-source-span="{{ edge.provenance.source_span }}"
          data-as-of="{{ edge.provenance.as_of }}">
          <span>{{ edge.edge_type }}</span><strong>{{ edge.source }} → {{ edge.target }}</strong>
        </button>
      {% endfor %}
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
  <aside id="e3-provenance" class="e3-provenance" aria-live="polite">
    <strong>Provenance receipt</strong>
    <span data-provenance-doc>Select a node or edge.</span>
    <blockquote data-provenance-span>Its exact authored source sentence will appear here.</blockquote>
    <span data-provenance-date></span>
  </aside>
</section>

<section class="e3-panel" aria-labelledby="e3-retrieval-title">
  <header class="e3-panel__head">
    <div>
      <p class="e3-kicker">Decision-hook query</p>
      <h2 id="e3-retrieval-title">“What did Corvid Lane say about liquidity in 2024?”</h2>
    </div>
  </header>
  <div class="e3-retrieval-grid">
    {{ passage_list('Lexical only', card_data.retrieval.lexical,
      'Literal terms work; the paraphrased meeting note ranks 5th.') }}
    {{ passage_list('Plain hybrid', card_data.retrieval.plain_hybrid,
      'Semantic meaning helps, but the Wexford distractor ranks 2nd.') }}
    {{ passage_list('Graph candidate', card_data.retrieval.graph_candidate,
      'One-hop entity scoping drops the wrong-firm distractor. Candidate only.') }}
  </div>
  <p class="e3-illustration"><strong>Illustrative top-3:</strong> recall
    {{ "%.2f" | format(card_data.retrieval.illustrative_k3.baseline.recall) }} →
    {{ "%.2f" | format(card_data.retrieval.illustrative_k3.graph_candidate.recall) }}.
    This is not the formal gate.</p>
</section>

<section class="e3-panel" aria-labelledby="e3-gate-title">
  <div class="power-gate e3-power-gate">
    <span class="power-gate__title" id="e3-gate-title">Formal recall@10 is insufficient</span>
    <p>The rule is <strong>+0.10 absolute recall@10</strong> and a
      <strong>paired interval lower bound above zero</strong>. The current fixture has one
      planted query, below the paired-evidence minimum.</p>
    <div class="e3-gate-metrics">
      <p><strong>Baseline recall@10</strong>
        {{ "%.2f" | format(card_data.retrieval_gate.formal_metrics.baseline.recall) }}
        <span>95% Wilson interval
          {{ "%.2f" | format(card_data.retrieval_gate.formal_metrics.baseline.recall_wilson[0]) }}–{{ "%.2f" | format(card_data.retrieval_gate.formal_metrics.baseline.recall_wilson[1]) }}</span></p>
      <p><strong>Graph-candidate recall@10</strong>
        {{ "%.2f" | format(card_data.retrieval_gate.formal_metrics.graph_candidate.recall) }}
        <span>95% Wilson interval
          {{ "%.2f" | format(card_data.retrieval_gate.formal_metrics.graph_candidate.recall_wilson[0]) }}–{{ "%.2f" | format(card_data.retrieval_gate.formal_metrics.graph_candidate.recall_wilson[1]) }}</span></p>
      <p><strong>Observed uplift</strong>
        {{ "%+.2f" | format(card_data.retrieval_gate.uplift) }}
        <span>No paired interval from one query.</span></p>
    </div>
    <p><strong>Result:</strong> active hybrid fallback. If the graph does not clear the
      baseline by the stated margin, E3 ships as extraction tables plus search, no production
      graph expansion.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="e3-panel" aria-labelledby="e3-brief-title">
  <header class="e3-panel__head">
    <div>
      <p class="e3-kicker">Decision hook</p>
      <h2 id="e3-brief-title">Document-native meeting brief</h2>
    </div>
  </header>
  <div class="e3-brief-grid">
  {% for section in card_data.brief.sections %}
    <article class="e3-brief-section" data-state="{{ section.state }}">
      <h3>{{ section.title }}</h3>
      {% if section.state == 'rendered' %}
        {% for row in section.views %}
          {% if row.quote %}<blockquote>{{ row.quote }}</blockquote>{% endif %}
          {% if row.question %}<p>{{ row.question }}</p>{% endif %}
          <span class="provenance-chip">{{ row.source_doc }} · {{ row.as_of }}</span>
        {% endfor %}
      {% else %}
        <p><strong>Not attached:</strong> {{ section.omitted.reason }}.</p>
      {% endif %}
    </article>
  {% endfor %}
  </div>
  <p>This is intentionally partial: there is no identity crosswalk to the existing M5/S2
    demo manager, so no foreign manager's figures are relabelled as Corvid Lane.</p>
</section>

<aside class="e3-honesty" role="note">
  <h2>Demo and live boundary</h2>
  <p>Dense scoring here is an <strong>authored concept-table stand-in</strong>, and every
    displayed fact is an authored synthetic constant. Live extraction requires
    precision and recall at least 0.8 per core slot <strong>before any real-document fact renders</strong>.
    The absent extraction harness is a live prerequisite, not something this demo pretends to run.</p>
  <p>The brief is <strong>help, not an audit</strong>. This product is not a chatbot, and a
    retrieved passage is preparation material, never a mechanical judgement.</p>
</aside>
{% endblock %}

{% block methodology %}
<p>E3 stores seven typed entity tables and six typed edge tables in standard-library SQLite.
  BM25 supplies literal matching, the disclosed concept table supplies the demo semantic
  channel, and reciprocal-rank fusion combines rank positions. The active output stops at
  hybrid search because the candidate graph has not cleared its formal paired retrieval gate.</p>
<p>Every fact carries a source document, exact sentence, and date. Graph expansion is one hop:
  documents attributed to the manager plus documents authored by people employed there. No
  graph database, two-hop theme walk, live embedding model, or real-document extraction is
  hidden behind this exhibit.</p>
{% endblock %}

{% block body_scripts %}
<script src="{{ asset_base | default('') }}assets/e3-knowledge.js"></script>
{% endblock %}
